I"Ó<h3 id="landing-page-layout">Landing page layout</h3>

<p>Located at <a href="https://github.com/18F/18f.gsa.gov/tree/master/_layouts/primary.html">_layouts/landing.html</a>, this is the layout that is used for the landing page on seedfund.nsf.gov.</p>

<h4 id="landing-page-general-front-matter">Landing page general front matter</h4>

<p>The primary template uses <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/docs/frontmatter/">Jekyll front matter</a> heavily to account for variations within the site. Below are the the potential front matter attributes that you can use. Some are listed as <em>(optional)</em>. These can be used to alter the appearance of a page.</p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Attribute</th>
      <th>Value</th>
      <th>Type</th>
      <th>What it does</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><code class="highlighter-rouge">title</code></td>
      <td><code class="highlighter-rouge">NSF SBIR</code></td>
      <td>String</td>
      <td>Title for the page visible in blue banner at the top of the page</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code class="highlighter-rouge">permalink</code></td>
      <td><code class="highlighter-rouge">/</code></td>
      <td>String</td>
      <td>Path that the page renders relative to the siteâ€™s <code class="highlighter-rouge">baseurl</code></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td><code class="highlighter-rouge">layout</code></td>
      <td><code class="highlighter-rouge">landing</code></td>
      <td>String</td>
      <td>Sets the page layout to <code class="highlighter-rouge">primary</code></td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

